    <layer level="2" name="Layer 2">
      <focus/>
      <content>FIPS 140-2 (legacy, retires 2026) vs. FIPS 140-3 (harmonized with ISO/IEC 19790:2012; testing via ISO/IEC 24759:2017 and NIST DTR). Key differences: Stricter entropy/randomness (approved sources like DRBG, validated conditioning; no weak system RNG). Detail Levels 1-4 requirements (e.g., Level 1: functional; Level 4: environmental failure protection).</content>
    </layer>
    <layer level="3" name="Layer 3">
      <focus/>
      <content>Step-by-step CMVP: 1) Vendor self-test; 2) Submit to NIST-accredited lab; 3) Lab tests per Implementation Guidance (IG), ISO 24759; 4) NIST review/certification. Examples: Entropy validation (post-compromise recovery, noise sources). Practical: Module testing labs, certificate lookup on NIST site.</content>
    </layer>
    <layer level="4" name="Layer 4">
      <focus/>
      <content>Link to cloud (e.g., HSMs in AWS/GCP), secure design (zero-trust via validated crypto), cross-domain (risk models in federal systems). Implications: Compliance mandates (e.g., FISMA); optimize entropy for IoT/high-scale. Create: Hypothesize module for hybrid cloud with Level 3 tamper protection.</content>
    </layer>
